 'E. JEAN CARROLL CASE: In 2019, advice columnist E. Jean Carroll accused Trump of raping her in a Bergdorf Goodman dressing room in the mid-1990s. Trump denied knowing her despite photographic evidence. In May 2023, a jury found Trump liable for sexual abuse and defamation, awarding $5 million. In January 2024, a second jury awarded $83.3 million more for continued defamation. Total: $88.3 million.',
 'TWENTY-SIX ACCUSERS: At least 26 women have publicly accused Trump of sexual misconduct: Jessica Leeds (groping on airplane, 1970s), Kristin Anderson (groping in nightclub, early 1990s), Jill Harth (attempted rape, 1993), Cathy Heller (forced kiss, 1997), Temple Taggart (forced kiss, 1997), Mariah Billado (dressing room intrusion, 1997), and 20 others spanning five decades. Their accounts are consistent with his own recorded statements.',
 'MISS UNIVERSE PAGEANT ABUSES: As owner of Miss Universe organization, Trump allegedly walked into dressing rooms while contestants were undressing. Multiple contestants from Miss USA, Miss Teen USA, and Miss Universe have confirmed this behavior. Teen contestants reported Trump entered while girls as young as 15 were changing. Trump confirmed this on Howard Stern, boasting that as owner he could"inspect"contestants.',
 'EMPLOYMENT DISCRIMINATION: Trump Organization faced multiple lawsuits alleging gender discrimination in hiring, pay, and promotion. Female employees reported being evaluated on appearance, subjected to sexist comments, and paid less than male counterparts. A 1980 federal lawsuit accused Trump of discriminatory hiring practices.',
