 'JOEL GREENBERG: Gaetz\'s close associate Joel Greenberg, former Seminole County Tax Collector, pled guilty to sex trafficking of a minor and agreed to cooperate with investigators. Greenberg was sentenced to 11 years.',
 'VENMO PAYMENTS: Investigators examined Venmo payments from Gaetz to Greenberg and from both men to multiple young women. The payments were labeled with references suggesting they were for sex.',
 'THE MINOR: A then-17-year-old girl was allegedly paid for sex by both Greenberg and Gaetz. Greenberg obtained a fake ID for her. She has reportedly cooperated with investigators.',
 'WITNESS COOPERATION: Multiple women have reportedly cooperated with the investigation, providing testimony about sexual encounters with Gaetz and the circumstances of payments.',
 'NO CHARGES: In February 2023, DOJ reportedly informed Gaetz\'s lawyers it would not charge him. The decision was controversial given the evidence and Greenberg\'s guilty plea to trafficking the same minor.',
 'HOUSE ETHICS INVESTIGATION: The House Ethics Committee investigated Gaetz for sexual misconduct, illicit drug use, sharing inappropriate images, and accepting gifts. Gaetz resigned from Congress before the report was released.',
 'THE ETHICS REPORT: After Gaetz\'s resignation, the Ethics Committee released its report finding substantial evidence of sexual misconduct with minors, drug use, and accepting improper gifts.',
 'TRUMP NOMINATION: Despite the investigation and ethics findings, Trump nominated Gaetz for Attorney General. Gaetz withdrew after the Ethics report details emerged.',
 'PATTERN: The case exemplified how powerful political figures can avoid accountability for conduct that would result in prosecution for ordinary citizens.',
